{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, the optimal thresholds for copra cluster tightly near 0.99 for most classes, dropping slightly to approximately 0.90 in the highest-mass bin.",
    "In contrast, vipr yields significantly lower thresholds, typically ranging between 0.53 and 0.62.",
    "This difference reflects the distinct behavior of the two architectures: copra produces more sharply peaked confidence scores, while vipr shows a broader, more distributed confidence spectrum, as also visualized in figure 5 and discussed in section 2.5.",
    "ResultsWe begin our analysis by visually comparing the predictions produced by our deep learning models to the ground truth.",
    "Figure 6 shows a representative example from the held-out test simulation, displaying a single-voxel thick slice of the 3D volume."
  ]
}